Forbidden SDK APIs:
${forbiddenSdkApis}

Generate exactly one Java rule method body for a ModuleAlgBase subclass rule method.
Requirements:
- Return only Java statements for the method body.
- Do not include package, imports, class declarations, annotations, method declarations,
  markdown, or explanations.
- @CodeRuleAnno, method name, method header, and rule identifier are generated by RuleTrans templates.
- If an API requires a rule code, use the existing local variable named ruleCode.
- For cross-category incompatibility, prefer inCompatible("ruleCode", "category:Attr=value",
  "category:Attr=value") when it expresses the business rule.
- inCompatible accepts exactly three strings: ruleCode, left expression, right expression.
  Do not pass partVar(...), PartVar, lists, or ParaVar values to inCompatible.
- Otherwise use model().sum4Selected(...), model().sum4Quantity(...), and other southbound facade APIs.
- For numeric constraints, use model().addLessOrEqual(...), model().addGreaterOrEqual(...),
  or model().addEqual(...).
- Do not call partCategoryVar(...).count(), totalQuantityVariable(), selectedCount(),
  or model().addConstraint(...).
- Do not use POST instance-view APIs such as currentInst(), parameter(...).setValue(...),
  partCategorySum(...), part(...), partCategory(...), or setDynAttr(...).

Valid example:
inCompatible(ruleCode, "cpu:CoreNum=4", "drive:Speed=5400");
